body: With $15 million on the table, the future of energy hangs in the balance—will we invest in the raw, unrelenting power of nuclear energy or the adaptable, renewable potential of biofuels? Nuclear promises unmatched efficiency, capable of powering entire cities with a single reactor, yet its costs, waste, and safety concerns loom large. On the other hand, biofuels offer a cleaner, more sustainable path, repurposing organic waste into usable energy, though scalability and energy density remain challenges. This decision isn’t just about dollars—it’s about the trajectory of global energy, the environment, and the legacy we leave behind. Which path secures the future?
